HEADWORD: Chloropal
<hw>Chlo*ro"pal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chlwro`s</grk> light green + E. <ets>opal</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A massive mineral, greenish in color, and
opal-like in appearance. It is essentially a hydrous silicate of
iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

